9/10
Your schema can answer every business question posed. Overdue books? `WHERE return_date IS NULL AND due_date < NOW()`. Most popular book? Count Borrowing rows grouped by book_id. Active members? Filter on `active_member`. Low stock? Compare `number_of_copies_available` to a threshold. This is exactly what we want at this level.
The schema directly supports the queries the question asks for — that's the bar at EASY.
